# ── Build output ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# /bin/  = `make binary` output (./bin/kloo)
# /dist/ = goreleaser output (cross-OS binaries, archives, checksums)
/bin/
/dist/

# ── Go compiled artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────
# Go builds straight to binaries (no separate build dir), so ignore loose
# compiled output, platform libraries, test binaries, and profiling output.
# NOTE: testdata/ is intentionally NOT ignored — in Go it holds committed test
# fixtures (the *.golden snapshots + request/response JSON the tests assert on,
# and the repomap node_modules fixture). Ignoring it makes `go test ./...` fail
# on a fresh clone / in CI.
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
*.out
coverage.out
*.prof

# ── Go tooling / workspace ──────────────────────────────────────
# go.work[.sum] is a *local* multi-module override — machine-specific, not committed.
go.work
go.work.sum
# vendor/ stays tracked IF you vendor deps; kloo uses the module cache, so ignore it.
/vendor/

# ── Agent / tooling scratch ─────────────────────────────────────
# .aider*    = aider chat history / tag caches
# .johnnyone/ = J1 worker inbox + scratch written into the repo during runs
.aider*
.johnnyone/

# ── Benchmark (Ionic acceptance harness) ────────────────────────
# The Ionic app is kloo's regenerable acceptance TARGET, not part of kloo. We
# commit only the harness (benchmark/assert.sh + README); the app trees are NOT
# committed — regenerate with `ionic start … tabs --type=angular` (see the README).
benchmark/fixture/
benchmark/reference/
# Generated run output / evidence snapshots (reproducible via the harness; stale
# the moment code changes). Covers benchmark/artifacts AND benchmark/*/artifacts
# (e.g. benchmark/memory/artifacts). The harness scripts + READMEs stay tracked.
benchmark/**/artifacts/

# ── Local env / secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Editor / OS noise ───────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
